10/01/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- A new border checkpoint between Albania and Greece will open by the end of this month.
Agreement on the new facility was reached recently between representatives of Saranda, Albania and the Greek municipality of Igoumenitsa.
They also discussed projects related to the development of regional infrastructure.
In other news, the Albanian Ministry of Tourism announced on Friday (7 January) the start of a large-scale effort to legalise illegal houses across the country.
The government set 24 March as the deadline for residents to submit applications to local authorities.
The ministry estimates there are around 500,000 illegally built houses in Albania.
(Albanian News - 08/01/05)
